    @if (IsToolActive(ToolRules))
    {
    <ToolPanel Id="@ToolRules" Title="Monte Carlo Rules" CssClass="band tool-panel formulas" Style="@ToolStyle(ToolRules)"
               Collapsed="@IsToolCollapsed(ToolRules)" CanMoveUp="@CanMoveToolUp(ToolRules)" CanMoveDown="@CanMoveToolDown(ToolRules)"
               OnToggle="ToggleTool" OnMoveUp="MoveToolUp" OnMoveDown="MoveToolDown" OnRemove="RemoveTool">
        <p><strong>Baseline:</strong> homes are back-played from construction year into <code>start year - 1</code>, so old homes may already have changed households before the validation window starts.</p>
        <p><strong>Special grids:</strong> Lammersville and Inter-Districts use fair grade shares; MHESD uses grades 9-12 only.</p>
        <p><strong>Ownership change:</strong> each home has a yearly chance to replace its household, with lower early-year turnover and forced turnover by year 50.</p>
        <p><strong>Children at move-in:</strong> the model draws a household child count from explicit 0, 1, 2, 3, and 4 child shares. Move-in age weights place those children into preschool, TK/K, elementary, middle, high school, or post-school bands.</p>
        <p><strong>Density:</strong> low/medium, medium-high, and high density homes apply common density factors plus child-number factors for 1st, 2nd, and 3rd children.</p>
        <p><strong>Special education:</strong> every child has a probability of receiving a special education attribute. Special education children keep their underlying age/grade for aging, but are counted in the Sp. Ed. reporting bucket while enrolled.</p>
        <p><strong>Build timing:</strong> each newly built home joins either the same school year or the next school year, controlled by the same-school-year probability.</p>
        <p><strong>New children after move-in:</strong> annual 1st, 2nd, 3rd, and 4th+ child probabilities control births/new preschool children after the household arrives.</p>
        <p><strong>Student exit:</strong> each enrolled student can leave district enrollment without a home ownership change; TK-8, high school, and special education students use separate exit probabilities.</p>
        <p><strong>Validation:</strong> results are averaged over all runs and compared year-over-year against total enrollment, grid spread, and smoothed grade-by-grade error. TK is excluded from grade validation.</p>
    </ToolPanel>
    }
    }
    </div>
}

